
[1]resident

   RES'IDENT, a. [L. residens.]

   Dwelling or having an abode in a place for a continuance of time, but
   not definite; as a minister resident at the court of St. James. A B is
   now resident in South America.

                                RES'IDENT, n.

   1. One who resides or dwells in a place for some time. A B is now a
   resident in London.

   2. A public minister who resides at a foreign court. It is usually
   applied to ministers of a rank inferior to that of embassadors.
